1
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,240
I need some advice.

2
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:53,360
Well, a friend of mine...

3
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:55,880
...ended up sleeping
with her close friend.

4
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:57,480
And now they're scared
everything will change.

5
00:00:57,480 --> 00:00:58,880
If you were them,
what would you do?

6
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:01,880
Don't tell me something happened
on the island that night.

7
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:04,160
Who is that?

8
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:05,880
Our VIP passenger for this flight.

9
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:07,000
Hello, Ms. Mintra.

10
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:07,640
Who is she?

11
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:09,640
Her name is Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

12
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,520
Cute...

13
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:11,600
Thank you.

14
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:12,720
Not you.

15
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:13,960
Excuse me...

16
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:14,960
Is she hitting on her?

17
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:30,200
After surviving
that bizarre island...

18
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:33,920
the way of life for this tribe
has changed.

19
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:36,640
Young men and women of
reproductive age...

20
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:39,080
are feeling restless
in their hearts...

21
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:43,080
dwelling on forbidden reproduction.

22
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:46,160
Meanwhile, the surviving boy...

23
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:47,880
continues his search for answers...

24
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:50,520
about his own roots.

25
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:54,560
As for a certain abandoned puppy...

26
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:58,560
he eagerly and anxiously
waits for his owner.

27
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:01,440
Wait, is there a dog here too?

28
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:03,360
Yeah, and what "boy"
are you talking about?

29
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:06,400
Well, I was just making stuff up for fun.

30
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,640
Since it was so quiet.

31
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:09,960
Ever since we got back
from that crazy island...

32
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:11,840
everything feels a bit strange,
doesn't it?

33
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,520
Maybe it’s because...

34
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:17,280
the most important person isn't here.

35
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,160
What?

36
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:20,120
I'm not missing Chaba at all.

37
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,640
It’s good that she resigned.

38
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:23,200
Running off to save her own skin like that.

39
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,040
Me?

40
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:26,680
I haven't thought about talking to her at all.

41
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,400
He meant Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

42
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:37,760
Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

43
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:39,200
I need some advice.

44
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,640
If I grow a mustache...

45
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:42,880
is it against the rules?

46
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:44,520
You can look it up in the manual.

47
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:46,480
It's starting to poke my nose.

48
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:51,480
Kree, is something wrong?

49
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:58,360
Are you worried about me?

50
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,560
Stop playing dress-up like a doll...

51
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:02,320
and get back to work.

52
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:10,840
Why doesn't she like
my mustache anymore?

53
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:13,200
You wearing a fake mustache like this...

54
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:15,720
makes her think you're a psycho.

55
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:18,760
How could you even think of this, moron?

56
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:20,720
Look at you guys...

57
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:26,600
What the hell is wrong with you?

58
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:27,200
Why did you shave your real mustache...

59
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,400
just to put on a fake one?

60
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:30,160
I didn't shave it!

61
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,560
Ever since I got back from that island...

62
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:33,200
my mustache just won't grow back at all.

63
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:35,440
No matter how hard I try to grow it,
nothing happens.

64
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:37,800
What the hell am I
supposed to do now?

65
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:42,960
Why does she seem
like a different person...

66
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,000
from when we were on the island?

67
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,520
What does she really think of me?

68
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:46,720
I seriously can't read her at all.

69
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:49,160
Or maybe it's like that Thai proverb
that says...

70
00:03:49,160 --> 00:03:51,560
a woman's feelings
are like fog and smoke.

71
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:52,640
Hard to read.

72
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:54,680
Since when does that Thai proverb
even exist?

73
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,360
Should I just ask her...

74
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:58,480
whether she is smoke or fog?

75
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:00,120
Which one is better anyway?

76
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,840
Hmm, fog.

77
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,760
Fog is beautiful
and makes you feel cool.

78
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,720
And what happens
when smoke gets in your eyes?

79
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:09,200
It makes you shed tears, man.

80
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:11,920
You just ripped off the concept
from Bird Thongchai's song.

81
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:13,760
What song? I'm just trying to say...

82
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,640
that Ms. Petchgam Ploy is like...

83
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:17,480
Like what?

84
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,880
Please get back to work.

85
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,520
Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

86
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:24,520
I seriously can't read you at all.

87
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:27,080
Is there something I said
that you don't understand?

88
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:29,080
Sometimes you're like fog...

89
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,640
but sometimes you're like smoke.

90
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:32,120
I'm starting to get unsure too.

91
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,800
But even if you're the smoke
from a fire I have to risk...

92
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,720
I'm ready to face it.

93
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,560
Back off.

94
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:40,600
Because I'm afraid
you'll end up shedding tears.

95
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:46,120
Wow, this is so musical.

96
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:48,320
Why don't you just buy the rights
and sing the whole song...

97
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,080
so you don't have to beat
around the bush with the lyrics?

98
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,280
Mr. Kreetha.

99
00:04:52,280 --> 00:04:55,000
I don't know if you actually
understand my orders or not.

100
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,840
Stop filling your head with nonsense.

101
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:58,400
Don't make me use hard measures.

102
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,640
Is this what you mean
by hard measures?

103
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:05,920
Ms. Petchgam Ploy...

104
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:06,360
What on earth?

105
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:07,440
No, that's not what it is!

106
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:08,000
Clear.

107
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,000
After you, Ms. Mintra.

108
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,600
Who is she?

109
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,720
Our VIP passenger for this flight.

110
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:19,600
Ms. Mintra...

111
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,280
the sole heiress...

112
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:22,800
to the Massive Universal Fortune...

113
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:26,280
...owner of a 6-star hotels
around the world, real estate global.

114
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:31,280
Hello, Ms. Mintra.

115
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:34,000
Uh, you can't pass through yet.

116
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,600
Whenever I try to do something
down-to-earth...

117
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,600
there’s always a problem.
Me, Ke!

118
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:43,480
Oh, what is going on here?

119
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,920
Wait, hold on a second.

120
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:48,680
Ms. Mintra.

121
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,240
Oh.

122
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,480
Oh, hold on a second.

123
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,680
Can you let me speak first?

124
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:55,000
Can you stop using money
to solve every problem?

125
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,880
Isn't money what everyone wants anyway?

126
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:58,480
For some people, maybe.

127
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,800
But for me right now...

128
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,640
I want you to tell your bodyguards...

129
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:03,040
to let go of my employee first.

130
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,040
He can barely breathe.

131
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:08,880
Ke.

132
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:15,240
Sky, take over from here.

133
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:17,240
Who does she think she is?

134
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:19,280
Her name is Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

135
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,160
Usually...

136
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:23,960
she works as a purser for the airline.

137
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:27,040
Today, she's a purser...

138
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:29,840
And does she usually talk...

139
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:31,720
to VIP passengers like this all the time?

140
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,720
Uh...

141
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:36,520
Nice. Cute...

142
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:37,760
I like that.

143
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:40,480
Oh, thank you!

144
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,480
Not you.

145
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:46,920
What a total bitch!

146
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:47,560
Did she just say...

147
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,480
that she likes Ms. Petchgam Ploy?

148
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:52,080
You totally misunderstood the situation.

149
00:06:52,080 --> 00:06:53,000
She likes me.

150
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:55,640
She's just using Petchgam Ploy
as a distraction.

151
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:56,040
Oh, really?

152
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:56,560
Yeah.

153
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:57,560
She likes you for sure...

154
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,200
And why are you standing there
looking so sad? You're crazy.

155
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,680
Gift.

156
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,880
Oh, look at this dog video.

157
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:13,200
The dog can dance too.

158
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,040
So cute.

159
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:14,880
Chaba.

160
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:15,840
Huh?

161
00:07:15,840 --> 00:07:17,600
I need some advice.

162
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:18,360
Huh?

163
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,800
Well, a friend of mine...

164
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,520
ended up...

165
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,560
sleeping with their close friend.

166
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,720
And now...

167
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,760
they're scared everything will change.

168
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:29,200
If you were them,
what would you do?

169
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,120
Do you actually have other friends?

170
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,520
Aside from us?

171
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,400
Yeah, I do.

172
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,960
She’s my childhood friend
who lived next door...

173
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:37,360
in my old neighborhood.

174
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,400
Right next door...

175
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,360
to my old, old house.

176
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:42,080
Oh, what a relief.

177
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:44,280
Otherwise, I would’ve thought
you were talking about Chai.

178
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:46,240
Why does it have to be Chai?

179
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,480
Well, messy drama like this...

180
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:49,400
usually only happens
to you and Chai, right?

181
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,720
What's wrong with you?
Want to throw up?

182
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:54,960
No, I'm fine.

183
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:56,320
Anyway, in conclusion...

184
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:58,600
if it were you, what would you do?

185
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:02,520
If it were me? Honestly...

186
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,320
Hey, everyone!

187
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:09,040
If I accidentally ended up
sleeping with my close friend...

188
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,560
Chaba, why the hell
are you live-streaming?

189
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:13,240
Gift, why do you have to
ruin my vibe?

190
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:16,120
Good content like this
is hard to come by, you know.

191
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,520
This is worth millions of views!

192
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,160
We can just talk among ourselves,
no need to live-stream.

193
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:21,240
What content?

194
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,520
The "sleeping with a close friend"
content.

195
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:24,560
Hey, no! Chaba's content!

196
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:27,520
I mean, whatever content
she makes is always great.

197
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:28,240
Right?

198
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:32,240
Right! I'm just talented.
Natural-born talent.

199
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:36,400
Okay, well, I'm heading out
to get some coffee.

200
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,080
Do you guys want any?

201
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:38,680
I'm good.

202
00:08:38,680 --> 00:08:39,920
Can I get some
deep-fried dough sticks?

203
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:41,120
Okay, I'll see if they have any.

204
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:44,280
What about you, Tid-Gift?
You don't want any?

205
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,640
A double-shot latte, less sweet...

206
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:48,600
the way you always like it.
Want one?

207
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:50,600
No.

208
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:53,960
Come on, just have one.
I'll buy it for you.

209
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,840
Oh, and one more thing...

210
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,080
I noticed the tissues are out.

211
00:08:58,080 --> 00:09:00,960
And I saw that your toothpaste
just ran out too.

212
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:04,960
I'll buy the same brand, same flavor...

213
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:07,320
about two tubes for you, okay?

214
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:09,200
It's fine. It's really fine.

215
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:11,200
Come on, I'll just get them for you.

216
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:16,240
Oh, and when I get back...

217
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:18,040
can we talk for a bit?

218
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:22,560
I'll be right back.

219
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:26,320
Talk about what?

220
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:27,960
How should I know?

221
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,760
I don't know,
and I don't want to talk.

222
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:39,560
Ms. Mintra.

223
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:41,200
The item you ordered is ready.

224
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,160
Thank you.

225
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:44,640
She seems pretty normal.

226
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:46,120
It doesn't look like
she likes Ms. Petchgam Ploy...

227
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,560
in that way or anything.

228
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:50,840
Here you go.

229
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,800
I noticed that the color
around the edge of your lips...

230
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,960
looks a bit faded.

231
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,720
Is it really that noticeable?

232
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:58,880
Not really.

233
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:00,440
It's just that
when I'm interested in someone...

234
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:02,160
I tend to stare at their lips.

235
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,160
Is she hitting on her?

236
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,120
I don't know...

237
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:09,200
but it's making me blush.

238
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,200
Is this what they call "shipping"?

239
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:20,560
You can't do that.

240
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:23,200
Uh, regulation number...whatever...

241
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:26,960
states that cabin crew
or pursers are forbidden...

242
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:30,960
from applying makeup
or touching up in front of passengers.

243
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,880
Oh.

244
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:36,640
In that case, if a passenger
is the one applying it for her...

245
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:39,080
it's not against the rules, right?

246
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,080
Excuse me.

247
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,400
Excuse me.

248
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:53,240
Thank you.

249
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:59,160
This isn't considered a violation, right?

250
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,480
No.

251
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:09,240
The seatbelt sign is on.

252
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:13,160
Okay, why don't you
return to your seat first?

253
00:11:13,160 --> 00:11:14,320
Whoa!

254
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:18,320
Whoa, watch out, watch out!

255
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:31,760
I'm not really okay.

256
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:34,040
But it feels perfect here.

257
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:36,040
Oh dear, watch out, watch out!

258
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:40,400
Are you okay?

259
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,440
I am not okay, All-New.

260
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:43,440
Highly not okay.

261
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:47,480
I'm so sorry.

262
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:52,360
Ms. Mintra,
if you need anything else...

263
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,640
please feel free
to press the call button.

264
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:54,320
In that case...

265
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:56,440
Ms. Petchgam Ploy,
could you press it for me?

266
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:58,440
Because what I really want right now
is your Instagram account.

267
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,480
Where is it?

268
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,080
Are you looking for this?

269
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:12,120
Oh, yes.
Give it back to me, please.

270
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:12,800
Sure.

271
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,200
But you have to answer me first.

272
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:17,000
Did you give Ms. Mintra
your Instagram?

273
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,240
Mr. Kreetha.

274
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,480
Give it back.

275
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:22,200
At first, you liked my rugged look.

276
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,600
So why are you into Yuri vibes today?

277
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,400
What kind of nonsense
are you talking about?

278
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,440
Give it back right now.

279
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:29,520
Stop denying your own feelings.

280
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,080
Does what happened on the island...

281
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,800
mean absolutely nothing to you?

282
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,200
I don’t want to hear
about this anymore.

283
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,280
Nothing happened.

284
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:42,040
Give it to me.

285
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:43,720
No.

286
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:47,440
Not until you answer me,
Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

287
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:49,000
This isn't a toy, Kree.

288
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,200
So, you'd better hand it over.

289
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,200
Whoa!

290
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:03,040
Kree! What did you just drop?

291
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:04,120
Do you have any idea that this tablet...

292
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:06,960
is the GA-3459_FD-456 model?

293
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:07,680
It's the tablet...

294
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:09,800
used to control
the aircraft's lighting system!

295
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:12,680
If it breaks,
it will cause a system malfunction.

296
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:14,240
This was the very
last batch manufactured.

297
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,840
And if it gets damaged or broken...

298
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:16,920
it means the entire system
in First Class...

299
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:19,360
will have to be
completely overhauled!

300
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:22,760
Uh, well...

301
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,840
It's entirely my fault.

302
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:27,120
It's not your fault.

303
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,880
Regulation 28 states that...

304
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,600
if any equipment is
damaged or broken...

305
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,840
while in the hands of the purser...

306
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:33,360
I must pay for the damages.

307
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:34,960
I’ll find the money to pay for it.

308
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,240
The total amount...

309
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:39,000
is 2.8 million.

310
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,840
If I pay two thousand a month...

311
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:41,920
how many months
will it take to cover it?

312
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:44,440
Like the company is
actually gonna wait for you, Kree.

313
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:45,760
Are you insane?

314
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,760
Who would ever let you
pay in installments?

315
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:50,440
No matter what,
I'll find the money to pay for it.

316
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:52,080
Regulation 29.

317
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,120
If the damage...

318
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:55,080
is irreversible...

319
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:57,320
the purser must be terminated immediately.

320
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,560
And the engineer who can fix the system...

321
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:03,000
has already gone back to Italy.

322
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,000
It's all over.

323
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:14,920
Gift, I don't get it at all.

324
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,520
Why the hell
do we have to come out...

325
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:18,440
and sit in the heat
just because of Chai?

326
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:21,080
What?
It has nothing to do with Chai.

327
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:23,720
Yeah, and it's not like
Chai tossed you out, right?

328
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:26,440
Tossed around?
What do you mean?

329
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:30,440
Tossed out! Not tossed around!
I said tossed out!

330
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:31,920
What the hell are you talking
about "tossed around"?

331
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:32,880
What is wrong with your ears?

332
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:36,080
Oh, since when did you guys
come outside?

333
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:38,800
Well, I told you I have something
to talk to you about.

334
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,320
Talk about what?

335
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:42,760
I'm not talking.

336
00:14:42,760 --> 00:14:44,400
What?

337
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,720
Did Chaba just fart?

338
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:47,640
What the hell...

339
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:49,680
Gift was trying to say that
I'm is sitting right here,

340
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:50,680
so don't talk yet.

341
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:51,800
Oh.

342
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:54,320
Well, Chaba is about to go live.

343
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:57,400
So I didn't want to disturb her
while she's trying to make a living.

344
00:14:57,400 --> 00:15:00,720
I wasn't even going to go live.

345
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:04,720
Look...

346
00:15:07,320 --> 00:15:08,560
Look, I really couldn't help myself.

347
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:11,040
I just couldn't hold back
my feelings anymore.

348
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:13,240
I know what I did might be wrong...

349
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:16,320
and it might make us
lose our friendship, but...

350
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,560
I'm sorry.

351
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,720
I really couldn't help myself.

352
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:24,880
- I told you not to bring up the island!
- I accidentally spilled your feminine wash!

353
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:28,200
What?

354
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,040
Don't you "what" me.

355
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:30,840
So, Tid-Gift here...

356
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:33,920
said don't talk about
what happened on the island that day.

357
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:35,040
While Chai over here...

358
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:38,240
said he used up all your feminine wash.

359
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,200
I'm seriously asking...

360
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,360
if I weren't here today...

361
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:41,760
would you two even be able
to communicate properly?

362
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:43,680
Oh.

363
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:45,560
Wait a minute...

364
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:47,080
You used up the entire red bottle...

365
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:49,240
that I ordered from France?

366
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,160
Uh, well, it was slippery...

367
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:56,160
and I accidentally knocked it over,
so it all spilled out.

368
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,760
I know it's impossible
to buy a new one...

369
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:00,080
but...

370
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:01,640
can I just say I'm sorry?

371
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:04,760
So you're acting all nice to me
just because you feel guilty, right?

372
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:05,520
Yeah.

373
00:16:05,520 --> 00:16:07,440
Oh.

374
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:09,120
You're not mad at me, right?
Please, please?

375
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:11,000
What a relief.

376
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,040
So what's the story about
you guys on the island?

377
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:15,680
Don't tell me...

378
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,960
something happened on the island
that night.

379
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:20,360
What is it?

380
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:24,360
Oh, it's just that...

381
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:26,080
Tid-Gift wanted me to
talk trash about you...

382
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,400
about how you ran away
back home alone...

383
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,120
and abandoned your friends.

384
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:31,760
Yeah, exactly!
That's it, that's exactly it!

385
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:32,760
You're such a good friend.

386
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:34,400
Yep, spot on.

387
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,400
And did you talk trash about me yet?

388
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,360
- Not yet.
- No way.

389
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,200
Good.

390
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:37,920
Can I talk trash now?

391
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:40,200
No, don't.
It's not good.

392
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,360
No need to talk trash, right?

393
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:41,960
Yeah.

394
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,480
Friends don't talk trash
about each other.

395
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:44,480
Right.

396
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:52,080
Hey, with the lighting system
malfunctioning like this...

397
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,400
once Ms. Mintra comes
out of the restroom...

398
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:56,520
what the hell are we gonna tell her?

399
00:16:56,520 --> 00:17:00,960
That "I, Kreetha,
former cabin crew...

400
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,960
broke the system myself"...

401
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:07,800
I already sent an email
to headquarters...

402
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:10,360
stating that I broke everything myself...

403
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:13,960
and that I’m willing
to pay for the damages.

404
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:16,960
It’s not Ms. Petchgam Ploy’s fault at all.

405
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,800
Mr. Kreetha...

406
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,160
So does this mean...

407
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:23,360
Kreetha is going to get fired?

408
00:17:26,360 --> 00:17:28,800
I’m willing to sacrifice
(sala) everything...

409
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:30,800
for you, Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

410
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,600
Oh, come on, All-New!

411
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:44,920
Why the hell did you
turn on the lights?

412
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:46,400
You completely ruined the mood.

413
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,720
I didn't even do anything.

414
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:50,640
How did the lights come back on?

415
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:53,800
Thank you for fixing it so quickly.

416
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,920
I appreciate it a lot.

417
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:56,920
Thank you.

418
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:01,480
Oh, see?
It’s already fixed.

419
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:02,960
Nobody has to lose their job anymore.

420
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,400
Uh, what happened?

421
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:08,360
Well, I happen to
own a hotel in Rome...

422
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:09,440
so I had my staff track down
the engineer...

423
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,280
until they found him.

424
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:12,120
Then he fixed the system...

425
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:13,600
via satellite from over there.

426
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:14,960
That was it.
Took just a second to finish.

427
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,840
Ms. Mintra, you are a genius!

428
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:18,720
That was absolutely fabulous!

429
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:21,520
No, it wasn't me.
The engineer did it.

430
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:24,120
Were you even listening?

431
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:26,320
She's getting on my last nerve.

432
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:28,520
I heard that loud and clear.

433
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:29,280
I heard it clearly too.

434
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:29,760
Yeah.

435
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:32,480
You're so dead.

436
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:34,400
Thank you so much, Ms. Mintra.

437
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,320
As for me...

438
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:36,760
I might have never
sacrificed (sala) anything...

439
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:38,880
for you before,
Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

440
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:40,320
But I’m certain that...

441
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:42,120
if you are with me...

442
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:43,560
you won't ever have to
sacrifice (sala) a thing.

443
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:51,720
Are we talking about
"Sala Sumalee" (the snake fruit)?

444
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:52,720
Shut the hell up.

445
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:11,240
Oh, you're back?

446
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:13,040
Are you hungry?

447
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,840
A little bit, yeah.

448
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,000
Come here.

449
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:21,120
Come eat this.

450
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:22,200
Eat what?

451
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:23,800
We aren't on the island anymore,
you know.

452
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,840
Here.

453
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:29,200
What kind of mood are you in
to want to eat mushrooms?

454
00:19:29,200 --> 00:19:31,200
Can't I eat mushrooms
whenever I want?

455
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:33,160
Are you missing grilled mushrooms
from the BBQ place?

456
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:35,200
Hey!

457
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:36,320
Hey, what's going on?

458
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:37,600
Wait, wait a second.

459
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:39,520
What the hell is this?

460
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:51,040
Doesn't this vibe feel familiar?

461
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:53,960
It makes me feel like...

462
00:19:53,960 --> 00:19:55,800
Like what?

463
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:57,400
Are you still thinking about
what happened on the island?

464
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,280
Huh?

465
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,480
It feels like we should play
with a spirit board...

466
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:04,320
A spirit board?

467
00:20:04,320 --> 00:20:05,920
Yeah, the vibe is just right.

468
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:08,000
What is wrong with you?

469
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,240
You keep talking about the island.

470
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,280
It's just that the atmosphere feels...

471
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:13,720
just like when we were on the island.

472
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:16,360
There's mushrooms,
dim lighting...

473
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:18,560
and here we are, just the two of us, like this.

474
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,680
And then...

475
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:21,320
Oh.

476
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:22,360
Yeah.

477
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:23,840
I haven't thought about it at all.

478
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:27,560
You haven't thought about it at all?

479
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:28,320
No.

480
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,360
Why would I think about it?

481
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:31,640
Today the lights went out,

482
00:20:32,360 --> 00:20:33,720
and that day there were no lights.

483
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:36,040
I don't see
how they're connected at all.

484
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:37,280
What is wrong with you?

485
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:38,800
Is there something bothering you?

486
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,440
You keep saying
"island, island, island."

487
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:43,680
Are you okay?

488
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:47,800
I'm fine.

489
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,960
What would I not be okay about?

490
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:52,960
Since we were drunk that day...

491
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:56,080
and bored,

492
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:58,520
we were probably just looking
for something to do to kill time.

493
00:20:58,520 --> 00:21:00,880
Yeah, exactly.
That's good.

494
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:03,760
Because we're a perfect match.

495
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:06,480
It’s fitting that we’ll be housemates...

496
00:21:06,480 --> 00:21:09,560
forever.
Right, wifey?

497
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:20,080
Hey, I’m going to go
make a phone call.

498
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,560
I just got a match,
isn't he handsome?

499
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:23,560
Yeah.

500
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:28,080
Good night, wifey.

501
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,320
Things are better this way.

502
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:48,000
The power's back on!

503
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,200
How’s it going?

504
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:08,200
Did HR cancel
your resignation in time?

505
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:11,240
Nope.

506
00:22:11,240 --> 00:22:13,320
They never received the email.

507
00:22:13,320 --> 00:22:15,640
I misspelled the email address.

508
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:17,720
Hey, you idiot!

509
00:22:17,720 --> 00:22:18,560
But at least...

510
00:22:18,560 --> 00:22:20,040
in your stupidity,

511
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:21,680
there’s still some good luck.

512
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,160
Then why the hell
do you look so sad?

513
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:24,280
Because no matter what I do...

514
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:26,160
I can't compete with Ms. Mintra at all.

515
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:27,280
I'm poor.

516
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:28,520
I suck at everything.

517
00:22:28,520 --> 00:22:32,240
Hey, the person who gets
to decide on that matter...

518
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:33,080
isn't you.

519
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,280
It's that person over there.

520
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:37,000
Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

521
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:38,480
Ms. Petchgam Ploy!

522
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,040
Hey!

523
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:44,000
I thought you said
Ms. Petchgam Ploy was here?

524
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,440
Who is this?

525
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:46,360
I didn't say that.

526
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:48,480
I just said the person who makes
the decision is sitting right over there.

527
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:55,560
And today,
I am representing Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

528
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:58,240
I have the authority
to make all decisions here.

529
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:04,520
Care to guess what my name is?

530
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:09,720
What is it?
A winged animal that cannot fly...

531
00:23:09,720 --> 00:23:11,760
but when it grows up...

532
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:14,520
it lays eggs.

533
00:23:14,520 --> 00:23:15,800
I'll give you a hint.

534
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:17,280
It goes...

535
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:19,240
Cluck, cluck, cluck!

536
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:20,280
Kreetha, you answer.

537
00:23:20,280 --> 00:23:21,760
Where is Ms. Petchgam Ploy?

538
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:23,360
I told you to answer,
not ask a question.

539
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:24,800
Come on,
just answer "Kai" (Chicken).

540
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:25,520
Wrong!

541
